  <recipe>
    <head>
      <title>'egg' Salad</title>
      <categories>
        <cat>Salad</cat></categories>
      <yield>4</yield></head>
    <ingredients>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>8</qty>
          <unit>ounces</unit></amt>
        <item>Tofu; medium firm, shredded</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>2</qty>
          <unit/></amt>
        <item>Green onions; chopped</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit>tablespoon</unit></amt>
        <item>Fresh parsley; chopped, or more</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit>teaspoon</unit></amt>
        <item>Curry powder</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1/4</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Mayo or almondaise (use your favourite)</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty/>
          <unit/></amt>
        <item>Salt + pepper to taste</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty/>
          <unit/></amt>
        <item>Paprika sprinkled on top</item></ing></ingredients>
    <directions>
      <step>  From: sylvia@itrc.on.ca
  
  Date:   Tue, 30 Jul 1996 10:25:42 -0400
  Mix the first six together until colour is consistent. For a large group,
  put lettuce leaves around the bowl first, pack in the 'egg' salad, then
  form a sunny happy face with a spoon. For some reason, people love it and
  get a real kick out of this.
  
